history.content:
The workload for CS 188 is not that different compared to Math 110, although the exams are notoriously hard. So decide which class is more important for you to take and pick accordingly. CS 170, as you might have heard, is difficult and takes significant time out of your schedule. CS 186 has moderate workload, with peaks during project deadlines.

For either of your options, your semester is definitely going to be busy.

--------------------

I'm taking 186, 170, and 110 right now and it's manageable. 170 definitely takes up the most time and 186 projects are very reasonable.

children.subject: Would you say that both of you have time outside of class for extracurriculars too?
Yeah, i have about ~15 hours of extra curriculars per week and I still have time to socialize and not do any work on Saturdays. My friend is in calband which takes a lot of time time too

My friend is actually taking 170, 186, 188 AND 110 right now. He's doing fine in the first 3 but has been neglecting 110 a LOT and is doing so well in it. So I think the first 3 is fine. I'm taking 170 188 and 110 right now (as well 2 P/NP breadths) and its not too bad.

history.content: Right now I am waitlisted for CS 170, 186, and 188 because I wanted to maximize my chances of getting at least 2 CS upperdivs (undeclared until next semester). In the unlikely event that I get into all 3, would that be doable? I am currently in Math 110 and getting into CS 188 would swap with that, so would CS170 + CS 186 + Math 110 be a better idea? Any comments about the workload of the 3 classes would be appreciated!
